# BIM Quality Validator Skill

## Overview
This skill provides validation checklists and procedures for ensuring Revit model quality after AI-driven operations.

## When to Use
- After batch element placement
- Before issuing construction documents
- When verifying PDF-to-Revit conversions
- Quality assurance reviews

## Validation Levels

### Level 1: Quick Check (After Each Operation)
Fast validation during active work:
- [ ] Element count changed as expected
- [ ] No error messages returned
- [ ] Elements visible in correct location

### Level 2: Batch Validation (After Major Operations)
After completing a set of related elements:
- [ ] All elements placed successfully
- [ ] No overlapping/duplicate elements
- [ ] Elements hosted correctly (doors in walls)
- [ ] Geometry is valid (no zero-length walls)

### Level 3: Model Validation (End of Session)
Comprehensive model quality check:
- [ ] Revit warnings resolved
- [ ] All rooms enclosed and tagged
- [ ] Schedules populate correctly
- [ ] Views display as expected

### Level 4: QC Review (Before Issue)
Full quality control before deliverable:
- [ ] Code compliance verified
- [ ] Coordination complete
- [ ] All annotations placed
- [ ] Print preview checked

## Validation Checklists

### Wall Validation
```
GEOMETRY
- [ ] All walls have non-zero length
- [ ] No duplicate/overlapping walls
- [ ] Walls properly joined at corners
- [ ] Wall heights consistent per level
- [ ] Base and top constraints correct

PROPERTIES
- [ ] Correct wall type assigned
- [ ] Structural parameter set correctly
- [ ] Location line consistent (finish face, centerline)
- [ ] Fire rating if required

CONNECTIVITY
- [ ] Exterior walls form closed perimeter
- [ ] Interior walls connect to exterior
- [ ] Room-bounding enabled where needed
```

### Door Validation
```
PLACEMENT
- [ ] All doors hosted in walls
- [ ] Door not at wall end (min 4" from corner)
- [ ] Door orientation correct (swing direction)
- [ ] Sill height appropriate

PROPERTIES
- [ ] Correct door type/size
- [ ] Mark (door number) assigned
- [ ] Fire rating if required
- [ ] Hardware group if needed

CLEARANCES
- [ ] Door swing doesn't hit other doors
- [ ] ADA clearances met (if applicable)
- [ ] Door opens into larger space (typically)
```

### Window Validation
```
PLACEMENT
- [ ] All windows hosted in walls
- [ ] Sill height consistent per type
- [ ] Head height clears ceiling
- [ ] Centered or properly aligned

PROPERTIES
- [ ] Correct window type/size
- [ ] Mark assigned
- [ ] Frame material correct
- [ ] Operation type (fixed, casement, etc.)
```

### Room Validation
```
ENCLOSURE
- [ ] All rooms fully enclosed by walls
- [ ] Room boundaries detected correctly
- [ ] Room areas calculating
- [ ] No "Not Enclosed" warnings

PROPERTIES
- [ ] Room names assigned
- [ ] Room numbers unique
- [ ] Department/function if needed
- [ ] Finish parameters populated
```

### Floor Validation
```
GEOMETRY
- [ ] Floor boundaries closed
- [ ] Floor at correct level
- [ ] Slopes defined if needed
- [ ] Openings cut for stairs/shafts

PROPERTIES
- [ ] Correct floor type
- [ ] Structural parameter correct
- [ ] Function parameter set
```

## Automated Validation Methods

### Using RevitMCPBridge
```
# Count elements by category
getElementsByCategory(category="Walls")
getElementsByCategory(category="Doors")
getElementsByCategory(category="Windows")
getElementsByCategory(category="Rooms")

# Get Revit warnings
getDocumentWarnings()  # If available

# Verify locations
getElementLocation(elementId=12345)

# Visual verification
captureActiveView()
```

### Comparison Workflow
```
1. Before placement:
   - Count existing elements
   - Note baseline state

2. After placement:
   - Count elements again
   - Expected: old_count + placed_count

3. Spot check:
   - Sample 3-5 elements
   - Verify locations match intent

4. Visual:
   - Screenshot active view
   - Compare to source data
```

## Common Issues & Solutions

### Geometry Issues
| Issue | Detection | Solution |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| Overlapping walls | Visual check | Delete duplicate, use wall joins |
| Gap in wall chain | Room not enclosed | Extend/connect walls |
| Zero-length wall | Build error | Delete, check input data |
| Misaligned walls | Visual check | Use align tool or edit endpoints |

### Hosting Issues
| Issue | Detection | Solution |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| Unhosted door | Warning or visual | Delete and replace in wall |
| Door at wall end | Visual check | Move door inward |
| Window above wall | Visual check | Lower sill or raise wall |

### Property Issues
| Issue | Detection | Solution |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| Wrong type | Schedule/properties | Change type parameter |
| Missing mark | Schedule empty | Assign marks manually/batch |
| Wrong level | Properties/visual | Move to correct level |

## Quality Metrics

### Acceptable Thresholds
```
Element placement success rate: > 95%
Location accuracy: within 0.1 feet (1.2 inches)
Type matching accuracy: > 90%
Manual corrections needed: < 5% of elements
```

### Warning Categories
```
CRITICAL (fix immediately)
- Elements not placed
- Wrong level/location
- Invalid geometry

IMPORTANT (fix before issue)
- Wrong types
- Missing properties
- Hosting issues

MINOR (fix if time permits)
- Suboptimal joins
- Inconsistent parameters
```

## Validation Report Template

```markdown
# BIM Validation Report

## Summary
- Date: [DATE]
- Model: [MODEL_NAME]
- Operation: [WHAT_WAS_DONE]
- Status: [PASS/FAIL/NEEDS_REVIEW]

## Element Counts
| Category | Before | After | Expected | Status |
|----------|--------|-------|----------|--------|
| Walls    | 0      | 24    | 24       | ✓      |
| Doors    | 0      | 8     | 8        | ✓      |
| Windows  | 0      | 12    | 12       | ✓      |
| Rooms    | 0      | 6     | 6        | ✓      |

## Issues Found
- None / [LIST ISSUES]

## Spot Check Results
- Wall #1: Location correct ✓
- Door #1: Hosted correctly ✓
- Window #1: Type correct ✓

## Recommendations
- [NEXT STEPS]

## Attachments
- Screenshot of floor plan view
- Before/after comparison
```

## Integration with Workflows

### After PDF Extraction
```
1. Compare detected element count to visual inspection
2. Verify scale by checking known dimensions
3. Validate wall continuity
4. Check door/window sizes are reasonable
```

### After Revit Placement
```
1. Run element count comparison
2. Take screenshot of floor plan
3. Compare to source PDF
4. Document any discrepancies
5. Note elements needing manual adjustment
```

### Before Session End
```
1. Run full validation checklist
2. Store session summary in memory
3. Note open issues for next session
4. Save model if validation passes
```
